Message.Title: Background task
Message.Description: refuse to start. Can't load module.
Message.Causes: The module file is missing in the target directory.
Message.Actions:
1. Copy the module file to the target directory.
2. Perform an I-start.

Message.Title: Task refuses to start
Message.Description:
Task :
There is not sufficient program memory or the program memory is fragmented. Modules could be missing or data may not have been installed.
Message.Actions:
1. Unload/reload modules and warmstart.
2. Split large data structures.
3. P-start the system.
4. Increase stack size for task.

Message.Title: A static/semistatic task can't be stepped
Message.Description:
Task can't be started.
A static/semistatic task can only run in continuous mode.
Message.Causes: Trying to step (forward or backward) a static/semistatic task.

Message.Title: Task could not be prepared for start
Message.Description:
Task :
There is not sufficient program memory or the program memory is fragmented. Modules could be missing or data may not have been installed.
Message.Actions:
1. Unload/reload modules and warm start.
2. Split large data structures.
3. P-start the system.

Message.Title: System diagnostics info unavailable
Message.Description: User requested to save diagnostics system information to file . System was unable to fulfill this request.
Message.Consequences: Diagnostics system information is normally used when reporting a problem with the system to ABB support.
Message.Causes:
The system is in such state that it is not possible to generate the requested information.
Please check that the device has enough space left.
Message.Actions: If you are experiencing a problem with the system contact ABB support.

Message.Title: Restore aborted due to lost system data.
Message.Description: The system is using a backup of the system data, since the system data was not properly saved at last shutdown. Due to this, a previously ordered Restore from directory was attempted again, but was aborted.
Message.Consequences: No RAPID programs or modules will be loaded.
Message.Causes: The system data was not properly saved at last shutdown.
Message.Actions: After recovering from the system data loss by a (B)ackup-Restart or system re-installation, please verify that the backup directory is OK, and perform the Restore again.

Message.Title: Restore error

Message.Title: New unsafe robot path
Message.Description: The robot path has been cleared after a target has been modified in task . The robot will for that reason move towards the position pointed out by the move instruction at the program pointer. Move instructions between the modified target and the program pointer will be skipped.
Message.Consequences:
The programmed speed is used for this movement.
The new untested path may contain obstacles that might cause a collision.
Message.Actions:
Check your program pointer and move it if necessary.
Reduce the speed.

Message.Title: Planned path not aborted
Message.Description: A target that may be part of the planned robot path has been modified. The new target position will be used the next time the instruction with the target is executed.
Message.Consequences: The current planned path is using the old target position.
Message.Actions: If the current planned path is unsafe, move the program pointer to abort it.
